class Solution {
    public int findLUSlength(String a, String b) {
        return a.equals(b) ? -1 : Math.max(a.length(), b.length());
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution directly compares the two input strings and returns -1 if they are equal, indicating that every subsequence of one string is also a subsequence of the other. Otherwise, it returns the maximum length of the two strings, which is the length of the longest uncommon subsequence. This approach has a constant time and space complexity, making it efficient for the given constraints.

